text: This weekend is the anniversary of the #WomensMarch, and as I’m in the other Washington fighting the Trump shutdown, seeing so many pictures from family and friends at marches this year is inspiring. Here’s one of mine from last year—can you share yours from this weekend? https://t.co/6s92Z8yaEP
This shutdown will impact families & communities in WA & nationwide if it's not ended quickly--it's time for Republicans to put people and families above partisanship and politics.
Now that Republicans have shut down the government, I am going to be doing everything I can to persuade the Republican majority to reopen the government and get to work with us.
Instead of working with us to get a result, President Trump and Republican leaders who control the House and Senate were more focused on pointing fingers and playing political games.
This is no way to run the government and no way to treat families looking to Congress for solutions, not dysfunction and uncertainty. #TrumpShutdown

One year ago, millions and millions of people across the country stood up at Women’s Marches nationwide to make clear that we were going to fight back against President Trump and his agenda https://t.co/8PdEeB8OXU
I am hopeful Republican leaders hear from the people they represent and reconsider this deeply damaging approach.

text: I am at the table and ready to get to work with anyone, from any Party, who is willing to work with those of us truly interested in getting results and passing legislation that keeps our government open and addresses the critical challenges facing our children and families.

Republicans and President Trump have pushed us from one short-term spending bill to the next. And now they are pushing us to the brink of a crisis. They’re more focused on playing politics than on working with us to get results.

Republican leaders have spent months refusing to work with Democrats on a long-term extension of the Children’s Health Insurance Program. They have blocked every effort to protect DREAMers in Washington state and across the country.

Democrats have made it clear we want to keep the government open to continue negotiations and reach a good result. If Republicans reject that and shut down the government, they'll be held accountable by people who will be paying the price for GOP dysfunction. #TrumpShutdown
There is absolutely no reason for the Republicans who control government to shut it down, and I am hoping they reverse course and work with us—today—to prevent that.
